<bioghist encodinganalog="545$a">
<head>Historical Information
</head>
<p>Nelson County was formed in 1807 from Amherst County. The county was named for Thomas Nelson Jr., governor of Virginia from June to November 1781.
</p>
</bioghist>
<scopecontent encodinganalog="520$a">
<head>Scope and Content
</head>
<p>Nelson County (Va.) Records, 1811-1931 (bulk 1811-1909), consist of the following Local Record categories: Bonds/Commissions/Oaths, Business Records, Court Records, Election Records, Fiduciary Records, Military and Pension Records, Organization Records, Tax and Fiscal Records and Wills.
</p>
</scopecontent>
